to keep this quiet?

90
00:09:51,507 --> 00:09:52,841
Please sit down.

91
00:09:53,259 --> 00:09:55,343
How could you do this alone?

92
00:09:56,012 --> 00:09:57,762
Well, l don't work alone.

93
00:09:57,972 --> 00:10:00,473
There's stuff in there I don't
understand. l'm really...

94
00:10:00,683 --> 00:10:02,392
...a systems manager. l farm...

95
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:05,729
...bits and pieces out to guys
who are more brilliant than l. I say:

96
00:10:05,896 --> 00:10:08,857
"Build me a laser, design me
a molecular analyzer" and they do.

97
00:10:09,025 --> 00:10:10,817
I just stick them together.

98
00:10:11,068 --> 00:10:13,778
But none of them knows
what the project really is. So....

99
00:10:16,198 --> 00:10:20,744
Wow. And the money?
Bartok Science lndustries financed this?

100
00:10:21,037 --> 00:10:24,247
Mm-hm. But they leave me alone
because l'm not expensive.

101
00:10:24,665 --> 00:10:27,584
And they know they'll end up
owning it all, whatever it is.

102
00:10:27,793 --> 00:10:30,629
-You haven't told them?
-When l'm ready.

103
00:10:30,796 --> 00:10:32,005
[TAPE RECORDER BEEPS]

104
00:10:32,173 --> 00:10:33,673
Wait a second.

105
00:10:35,801 --> 00:10:37,385
What's that?

106
00:10:38,054 --> 00:10:42,182
-You want me to get the quotes right.
-Quotes? No, no.

107
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:44,726
I thought this was personal.
You can't write about it.

108
00:10:46,062 --> 00:10:48,521
What are you talking about?
I'm a journalist.

109
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:51,608
-Oh, no, no, no.
-You knew that.

110
00:10:52,735 --> 00:10:56,821
I'm sorry, I made a mistake. I shouldn't
have shown you this. l'm very sorry.

111
00:10:57,865 --> 00:11:01,910
Listen. Particle Magazine sent me
to that party to get a story.

112
00:11:02,119 --> 00:11:04,496
And this is the most exciting thing
I've ever seen.

113
00:11:04,705 --> 00:11:07,290
No. Absolutely not.
I'm gonna have to ask for that tape.

114
00:11:07,458 --> 00:11:08,958
-Please.
-You can't do that.

115
00:11:09,126 --> 00:11:10,418
Don't you dare write a story.

116
00:11:10,586 --> 00:11:12,671
I'd never have told
this stuff to a journalist.

117
00:11:12,838 --> 00:11:16,424
-But you did tell it to a journalist.
-ln a way, l suppose l did but--

118
00:11:16,592 --> 00:11:19,052
-Sure did.
-Now wait a minute. Wait a minute.

119
00:11:19,637 --> 00:11:21,930
Wait. Come here.
What about your stocking?

120
00:11:22,348 --> 00:11:24,307
Keep it for good luck.

121
