135
00:12:10,146 --> 00:12:12,313
-And you fell for it.
-Wait a minute.

136
00:12:12,523 --> 00:12:14,357
-That was no night--
-Are we having lunch?

137
00:12:14,525 --> 00:12:18,194
Listen. That was no nightclub routine.
I was there. l saw it.

138
00:12:20,698 --> 00:12:21,948
Yup?

139
00:12:24,201 --> 00:12:25,452
Sure.

140
00:12:26,036 --> 00:12:27,537
Send him in.

141
00:12:28,831 --> 00:12:31,166
You must have made an impression.

142
00:12:31,542 --> 00:12:32,584
What do you mean?

143
00:12:33,169 --> 00:12:35,211
Your magician has followed you here.

144
00:12:35,379 --> 00:12:37,088
[KNOCKlNG]

145
00:12:38,632 --> 00:12:41,634
I'm Stathis Borans.
I'm the editor of Particle Magazine.

146
00:12:41,844 --> 00:12:44,888
-Seth Brundle.
-l know who you are.

147
00:12:45,097 --> 00:12:49,642
Listen, why don't you two use
my office? I've gotta run.

148
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:53,229
If you plan to make anything
disappear, please let me know.

149
00:12:53,481 --> 00:12:56,983
I've got an assistant editor
who's outlived his usefulness.

150
00:13:01,947 --> 00:13:03,239
You didn't waste any time.

151
00:13:04,116 --> 00:13:06,159
I'm not getting any younger.

152
00:13:08,621 --> 00:13:10,872
He wasn't impressed by your tape?

153
00:13:12,708 --> 00:13:14,042
He thinks you're a con man.

154
00:13:17,254 --> 00:13:18,630
-Excellent.
-Yeah?

155
00:13:18,798 --> 00:13:21,466
Well, let's see what the people
at Omni think about it.

156
00:13:21,675 --> 00:13:23,968
No, no. Listen, Veronica....

157
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:28,473
I've come here
to say one magic word to you.

158
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:31,434
Yeah?

159
00:13:31,602 --> 00:13:32,685
Cheeseburger.

160
00:13:38,150 --> 00:13:40,360
I've been working alone too long.

161
00:13:42,029 --> 00:13:45,406
I have a strong urge
to talk about what l'm doing.

162
00:13:46,408 --> 00:13:49,202
But if this gets out now...

163
00:13:49,411 --> 00:13:51,412
...Veronica, it'll kill me.

164
00:13:52,081 --> 00:13:54,791
The Bartok people
and my colleagues will kill me.

165
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:57,085
It's not ready yet.

166
00:13:57,336 --> 00:13:58,753
It seems to work okay.

167
00:13:59,088 --> 00:14:01,339
No, something important's missing.

168
00:14:01,757 --> 00:14:03,341
Yeah?

169
00:14:04,051 --> 00:14:05,134
Yeah.

170
00:14:07,555 --> 00:14:08,847
Which is?

171
00:14:10,641 --> 00:14:13,560
I can only teleport inanimate objects.

172
00:14:16,397 --> 00:14:18,690
What happens when you
try to teleport living things?

173
00:14:20,442 --> 00:14:21,526
Not while we're eating.

174
00:14:22,319 --> 00:14:24,362
Can't be worse than this.

175
00:14:27,825 --> 00:14:30,451
Listen, you're not doing a very good job
of convincing me.

176
00:14:30,661 --> 00:14:34,372
I think the world should know about it now.
I think I should be the one to tell it.

177
00:14:34,832 --> 00:14:36,457
You should tell it...

178
00:14:36,625 --> 00:14:41,212
...but not yet.
Look, what do you got so far?

179
00:14:42,047 --> 00:14:43,548
Enough to make you nervous.

180
00:14:43,757 --> 00:14:46,134
Why not get more?
Let me become your major project.

181
00:14:46,302 --> 00:14:48,469
I'm talking about a book,
not a magazine article.

182
00:14:48,637 --> 00:14:52,932
Follow me and my work day by day
in as much detail as you can stand.

183
00:14:53,601 --> 00:14:57,645
I don't have a life, so there's
nothing for you to interfere with.

184
00:14:57,855 --> 00:15:01,566
Research the background.
Cover the process.

185
00:15:02,776 --> 00:15:06,070
"The complete record of the most
earth-shattering invention ever.

186
00:15:06,322 --> 00:15:09,782
The one that ended
all concepts of transport...

187
00:15:09,992 --> 00:15:12,952
...of borders and frontiers,
of time and space."

188
00:15:15,581 --> 00:15:18,333
And the book'll end with me...

189
00:15:18,542 --> 00:15:22,003
...transporting myself 1 5 feet through
space from one telepod to another.

190
00:15:22,212 --> 00:15:23,504
That's what's really missing.

191
00:15:26,717 --> 00:15:28,134
Wait for me that long?

192
00:15:45,694 --> 00:15:48,029
[SHOWER RUNNING]

193
00:16:15,849 --> 00:16:17,850
What are you doing in my apartment?

194
00:16:18,268 --> 00:16:21,145
Just happened to be in the neighborhood.
Felt a bit scummy.

195
00:16:23,148 --> 00:16:24,691
Rough day.

196
00:16:27,861 --> 00:16:29,612
[FLUSHES TOlLET]

197
00:16:29,863 --> 00:16:32,323
[STATHlS YELLS]

198
00:16:35,494 --> 00:16:36,911
How did you get in?

199
00:16:38,414 --> 00:16:40,373
I have a key, remember?

200
00:16:40,791 --> 00:16:41,958
You gave it to me.

201
00:16:42,418 --> 00:16:44,669
I knew l should've changed the lock.

202
00:16:45,379 --> 00:16:46,879
I knew you wouldn't.

203
00:16:47,297 --> 00:16:49,465
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

204
00:16:50,342 --> 00:16:53,970
That's because unconsciously...

205
00:16:55,723 --> 00:16:59,017
...you still want me to come back,
move in again.

206
00:16:59,309 --> 00:17:00,435
No.

207
00:17:01,145 --> 00:17:05,648
That's because, very consciously,
I'm lazy and disorganized.

208
00:17:11,071 --> 00:17:12,822
Your new playmate's an interesting guy.

209
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:14,407
What playmate?

210
00:17:14,783 --> 00:17:16,492
The nightclub act.

211
00:17:18,370 --> 00:17:19,620
Brundle.

212
00:17:20,914 --> 00:17:23,082
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

213
00:17:24,752 --> 00:17:28,296
Yeah, l was wrong.
He's really quite brilliant.

214
00:17:29,965 --> 00:17:33,718
He was the leader of the F32 team.
Remember that?

215
00:17:34,970 --> 00:17:38,056
An inch away from the
Nobel Prize for physics.

216
00:17:38,557 --> 00:17:40,850
He was only 20 at the time.

217
00:17:41,477 --> 00:17:45,396
I don't even think l'll do Brundle. l'm
still considering the Psychology Today gig.

218
00:17:46,023 --> 00:17:47,190
That's not like you.

219
00:17:48,984 --> 00:17:51,235
Are you getting out or am l?

220
00:17:52,946 --> 00:17:56,657
I'll go. I have to put this issue to bed.
Want me to come back and tuck you in?

221
00:17:57,201 --> 00:17:59,118
No. Key.

222
00:18:01,163 --> 00:18:02,747
I'll keep it...

223
00:18:03,749 --> 00:18:05,124
...for old time's sake.

224
00:18:07,377 --> 00:18:09,587
You're a petty schmuck.

225
00:18:30,692 --> 00:18:33,111
Initiate in five seconds.

226
00:19:35,090 --> 00:19:37,633
[SQUEALING]

227
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:55,735
I've gotta do this, Seth.

228
00:19:55,986 --> 00:19:57,904
Talk to the tape. Get in the habit.

229
00:19:58,071 --> 00:20:00,114
The world will wanna know
what you're thinking.

230
00:20:00,282 --> 00:20:02,200
"Fuck" is what I'm thinking!

231
00:20:02,701 --> 00:20:03,910
Good.

232
00:20:04,119 --> 00:20:06,621
The world will wanna know that.

233
00:20:08,081 --> 00:20:10,249
What else? Why didn't it work?

234
00:20:11,001 --> 00:20:14,253
I think it turned the baboon
inside out.

235
00:20:17,549 --> 00:20:18,633
Why?

236
00:20:19,927 --> 00:20:22,845
Can't deal with the flesh.
It only works with inanimate objects...

237
00:20:23,013 --> 00:20:24,764
...nothing that's living.

238
00:20:27,184 --> 00:20:28,768
It must be my fault.

239
00:20:29,686 --> 00:20:31,270
Why?

240
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:36,108
Computers are dumb.
They only know what you tell them.

241
00:20:37,694 --> 00:20:41,197
I must not know enough about
the flesh myself. I'm gonna have to learn.

242
00:20:45,827 --> 00:20:48,079
I don't wanna talk now.

243
00:21:07,349 --> 00:21:09,558
Do you ever change your clothes?

244
00:21:10,978 --> 00:21:12,436
What?

245
00:21:13,230 --> 00:21:16,232
The clothes. You're always
wearing the same clothes.

246
00:21:19,569 --> 00:21:23,948
No, these are clean.
I change my clothes every day.

247
00:21:33,250 --> 00:21:35,668
Five sets of exactly the same clothes?

248
00:21:36,295 --> 00:21:37,378
Learned it from Einstein.

249
00:21:38,797 --> 00:21:40,381
This way l don't have to...

250
00:21:40,590 --> 00:21:44,969
...expend any thought on what l'll wear.
I just grab the next set on the rack.

251
00:21:51,643 --> 00:21:55,479
I bought some steaks.
Can l make you one?

252
00:21:56,565 --> 00:21:57,732
We could go out.

253
00:21:58,984 --> 00:22:00,151
Cheeseburger?

